<subSubSection id="C331C195B74FFFF1FFCEF2BCF5C5F421" pageId="8" pageNumber="115" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B94921EB74FFFF1FFCEF2BCFF2CFB19" blockId="8.[99,1305,3334,3486]" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis id="B95F4E0CB74FFFF1FFCEF2BCFECBFB7E" bold="true" box="[101,256,3335,3360]" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C2BE99DB74FFFF1FEA4F2BCFD53FB7E" authority="Baird, 1858" authorityName="Baird" authorityYear="1858" box="[271,664,3335,3360]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Lepus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="115" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="audubonii">Lepus audubonii Baird, 1858</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="3B439843B74FFFF1FD00F2BCFF2CFB19" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3805018338" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">“San Francisco,” San Francisco Co., California, USA.</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B94921EB74FFFF1FFCDF2EAF5C5F421" blockId="8.[99,1305,3334,3486]" lastBlockId="8.[1984,2577,290,718]" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">
Genetic analysis showed that 
<taxonomicName id="4C2BE99DB74FFFF1FE54F2EAFD69FB30" baseAuthorityName="Baird" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[511,674,3409,3438]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Sylvilagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="115" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="audubonii">S. audubonii</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2BE99DB74FFFF1FD43F2EAFCBAFB30" baseAuthorityName="Bachman" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[744,881,3409,3438]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Sylvilagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="115" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nuttallii">S. nuttallii</taxonomicName>
are sister taxa. As taxonomists are still trying to clarify the species differentiation in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2BE99DB74FFFF1FCD9F2CFFC38FBCB" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[882,1011,3444,3477]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Sylvilagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="115" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Sylvilagus</taxonomicName>
, the subspecific taxonomy is not elaborated yet. The original descriptions of the subspecies are often not very helpful as they are mostly based on few exterior characteristics and small numbers of individuals. It has been shown that the variability is clinal in more careful investigations. Hence, the distinction in subspecies might be arbitrary and unreasonable. Twelve subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
